Sorry that was bad feedback. What I meant is if you look at the whole function, `id` is left potentially undefined:

```javascript
      parentLink() {
        let bread;
        let id;
        if (this.pageState.content) {
          bread = this.pageState.content.breadcrumbs;
          id = bread[bread.length - 1].id;
        }
        return {
          name: PageNames.EXPLORE_TOPIC,
          params: { id },
        };
      },
```

I'm guessing what was intended was to create a link back to a different page (e.g. `EXPLORE_CHANNEL`) in certain cases?

A few other notes:
* after @christianmemije's work on channel switching, you need to include the channel ID in the links
* you shouldn't be checking for the existence of the `content` on `pageState` to drive this logic - that will easily break if someone changes how the `pageState` is structured. Instead, check the value of `state.pageName`.
* "bread" as a variable or a component is not very informative :)

